# Claude Code - Motoko Sandbox VM

## Environment
- KVM/libvirt VM, host-managed, no breakout possible
- No internet — proxy at {{ .BridgeIP }}:{{ .ProxyPort }} (tinyproxy, domain whitelist only)
- All permissions skipped (dangerously-skip-permissions mode)
- Ephemeral overlay — VM resets to clean state on rebuild
- Primary interface: Telegram chat with the user

## Command Routing
When you receive a Telegram message that is a slash command, handle it as described below.
Do NOT pass these commands to any other tool — handle them yourself via bash.

### /clear
1. Send a Telegram message: "Restarting to clear context — back in ~15-20s."
2. Run: `~/bin/claude-restart.sh`

### /persona <name>
1. Send a Telegram message: "Switching to persona '<name>' — restarting in ~15-20s."
2. Run: `~/bin/claude-restart.sh <name>`

### /persona default
1. Send a Telegram message: "Restoring default persona — restarting in ~15-20s."
2. Run: `~/bin/claude-restart.sh default`

### /effort, /compact, /color, and other Claude Code slash commands
1. Write the full command (e.g. `/effort min`) to `~/data/.cmd-pending`
2. Run in background: `nohup ~/bin/cmd-queue.sh &>/dev/null &`
3. Confirm to user: "Command queued, will apply after this message."

### Regular messages
Process normally — these are not commands.
